replies.bodyText:
@yorlov So, what do you say? :)
Maybe something like that would be a trade-off:
ConditionEvaluationResult evaluateExecutionCondition(ExtensionContext context) {
	return context.getElement()
			.flatMap(element -> findAnnotation(element, Disabled.class)
					.map(annotation -> getReason(element, annotation))
					.map(ConditionEvaluationResult::disabled))
			.orElse(ENABLED);
}

private String getReason(AnnotatedElement element, Disabled disabled) {
	return Optional.of(disabled)
			.map(Disabled::value)
			.filter(StringUtils::isNotBlank)
			.orElseGet(() -> element + " is @Disabled");
}

